yuhujdk8 - Enhanced OpenJDK 8 with Yuhu Interpreter and Compiler
========================================================================

Overview:
  yuhujdk8 is an enhanced OpenJDK 8 distribution that integrates Amazon Corretto 8 
  aarch64 source code and introduces the innovative Yuhu interpreter and Yuhu compiler.
  This project provides full support for the ARM64 (AArch64) architecture while 
  maintaining compatibility with existing OpenJDK 8 features.

Key Features:
  * Based on OpenJDK 8 - Maintains full compatibility with standard OpenJDK 8
  * Corretto 8 Integration - Incorporates Amazon's proven aarch64 improvements
  * Yuhu Interpreter - Advanced interpretation engine for AArch64 platform
  * Yuhu Compiler - LLVM-based JIT compiler with full bytecode-to-native compilation
  * AArch64 Support - Fully optimized for ARM64 architecture

Implementation Status:
  ✅ Core Infrastructure - Complete (ORC JIT, CompileBroker integration)
  ✅ Compilation Trigger - Complete (complexity-based selection with thresholds)
  ✅ Code Generation - Complete (bytecode to LLVM IR, stack frames, parameter passing, synchronized locks)
  ✅ Stack Frame Management - Complete (interpreter-compatible layout, traversal)
  ✅ Safepoint Mechanism - Complete (OopMap generation, GC integration)
  ✅ Lock/Monitor Support - Complete (synchronized semantics with CAS fast-path)
  ⚠️ Runtime Support - Partial (deoptimization and exception handling improving)
  ⚠️ Optimizations - Limited (relies on LLVM defaults, no inlining)

Platform Requirements:
  * Architecture: AArch64 (ARM64) only - Yuhu interpreter and compiler are currently
    optimized exclusively for AArch64 architecture
  * Compiler: Clang compiler required for building Yuhu components

Repository Structure:
  This repository contains the complete OpenJDK forest with the following 
  nested repositories:
    "jdk", "hotspot", "langtools", "corba", "jaxws", "jaxp"

Build Instructions:
  
  Prerequisites:
    - GNU make 3.81 or newer
    - JDK 7u7 or newer for bootstrapping
    - Clang compiler (required for Yuhu components)
    - Standard development tools for AArch64 platform
  
  1. Clone the repository:
       git clone git@github.com:liuanyou/yuhujdk8.git yuhujdk8
       cd yuhujdk8
  
  2. Configure the build:
       ./configure \
         --with-freetype-include=/opt/homebrew/Cellar/freetype/2.13.3/include/freetype2 \
         --with-freetype-lib=/opt/homebrew/Cellar/freetype/2.13.3/lib \
         --with-debug-level=slowdebug \
         --enable-yuhu-compiler=yes \
         --with-llvm=/opt/homebrew/Cellar/llvm/20.1.5 \
         --with-zstd-lib=/opt/homebrew/Cellar/zstd/1.5.7/lib \
         --with-boot-jdk=/Library/Java/JavaVirtualMachines/amazon-corretto-8.jdk/Contents/Home
  
  3. Build yuhujdk8:
       make images
     
     The resulting JDK image will be in build/*/images/j2sdk-image
  
  4. Test Yuhu Compiler:
     cd test_yuhu && ./test_matrix.sh
     
     This script verifies that the Matrix.multiply method is compiled by the Yuhu compiler.
     It will automatically detect the built JDK and run the matrix multiplication test.

